gdn.sh — PoHW Verification Node [00]
══════════════════════════════════════

STATUS: Active
PROTOCOL: Proof of Human Work v1.0.0
SIGNATURE FORMAT: SHA-256 • Ed25519
NODE TYPE: Public Verification Node

OVERVIEW
────────
This node provides stateless verification endpoints for Proof of Human Work
attestations. It operates as Layer 4 (Retrieval) of the PoHW protocol stack,
enabling open verification of authorship proofs without requiring trust in
centralized authorities.

VERIFICATION ENDPOINTS
──────────────────────
GET /pohw/verify/index.json
  Returns: Node status, protocol version, latest attestation hash, timestamp

GET /pohw/verify/index.cjson
  Returns: Canonical JSON (sorted keys, no whitespace) for cryptographic hashing

GET /pohw/verify/index.sig.bin
  Returns: Binary signature file (RSA PKCS#8) of canonical JSON

GET /pohw/verify/index.sig.b64
  Returns: Base64-encoded signature (alternate format)

VERIFICATION PROCESS
────────────────────
1. Upload file + signature
2. Node verifies signature against public key
3. Returns verdict: valid/invalid + signer DID + timestamp

PUBLIC KEY
──────────
Location: https://gdn.sh/.well-known/public.txt
Format: SSH Ed25519 public key
Fingerprint: SHA256:361132bb73b257cb8fcb0001d2328005f6b33b6ac5359f2394bc01c7571cc646

PROTOCOL SPECIFICATION
──────────────────────
Full standard: https://proofofhumanwork.org/spec
Registry: https://proofofhumanwork.org

NODE OPERATION
──────────────
This node:
• Accepts verification requests
• Validates signatures cryptographically
• Provides public verification endpoints
• Maintains node status and metadata
• Anchors to registry at proofofhumanwork.org

For registry node operation, see: https://proofofhumanwork.org/registry
